  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the dataset incorporates data from a smartwatch worn by the user, providing micro-localization information (based on an infrastructure using Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) beacons) at the room level.We performed our experiments only considering the single-inhabitant scenarios.",
    "Moreover, while the dataset also included inertial sensor data from the smartwatch (e.g., continuous acceleration on three axes), we ignore this type of data as it can not be directly transformed into a prompt in natural language.The dataset includes the following 13 activities: answering phone, clearing table, preparing hot meal, preparing cold meal, eating, entering home, leaving home, making phone call, setting up table, taking medicines, using PC, washing dishes, and watching TV.In our experiments, we do not consider the washing dishes activity since it is mainly characterized by inertial sensors in smartwatch data (not used by ADL-LLM).",
    "Moreover, we merged the making phone call and answering phone call activities into a single activity called phone call.",
    "UCI ADL.The UCI ADL dataset [39] includes data about the ADLs performed by two subjects in their own homes.",
    "The two homes are named Home A and Home B in the dataset."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "UCI ADL.The UCI ADL dataset [39] includes data about the ADLs performed by two subjects in their own homes."
  ]
}